Diabetes management in older people: a focus on cardiovascular risk reduction.

McNicholas E(1), Abdelhafiz AH(1).

Author information:
(1)a Department of Geriatric Medicine , Rotherham General Hospital , Rotherham , 
UK.

Cardiovascular disease remains the most common cause of death in persons with 
diabetes regardless of age. Increasing age combined with diabetes exert a 
synergistic effect on the vascular system increasing the atherosclerosis burden 
in older people with diabetes. Due to their high baseline risk, they stand to 
benefit most from interventions to reduce cardiovascular risk. Older people with 
diabetes are functionally heterogeneous and their management is challenging. Fit 
and independent individuals are likely to benefit from tight targets while a 
relaxed approach putting quality of life at the heart of management plans is 
more appropriate in the frail and dependent individuals with limited life 
expectancy.

